						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar built into the wall of a <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the south-east corner of Parāśarēś vara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja I (?) Year 23: 1008 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription seems to record the gift of gold on the 80th day of the 23rd year of Rājarāja I, referred to in No. 297 above as the subject of a dispute between the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tiruchchukanūr, and the <hi rend="italic">tāṉattār</hi> of the temple. The donor Nambaṉ Kūttāḍi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Jayaṅgoṇḍa-Śōḻamārāyan was a general of Rājarāja I.</p>						

						<p>This is a record of a gift of gold weighed by <hi rend="italic">Danmakaṭṭaḷaikkal</hi> by Nambaṉ Kūttāḍi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa Brahmamārāyan.</p>						

						</summary>
